The Alcohol Remote Monitoring System, or ARMS, is aimed towards those who find it difficult to drink responsibly without the aid of others, or those who may not have an immediately available support system when under the influence. Our aim for this project is to improve the emotional and physical well-being of our demographic by providing an easy way to avoid irresponsible behavior, or to aid them if they are unable to arrange convenient transportation...

Conceptualized and created by Jeff Meyers, Rob Lathrop, Sam Hemingway, and Steve Hsieh.